caption.text: Another compilation of random pictures I took at London. There was a bicycle event that blocked almost all major streets at London that day so please excuse all the biker photobombs.
Spending the weekend in London. Here's a compilation of random pics I took yesterday.

Last night's opening reception dinner. They prepared multiple well-dressed servers to serve us LOL. Dinner was a four-course meal inside a Hogwart-like dining hall, lit by real candles, surrounded by paintings and murals from the 1600s (just a guess, clearly renaissance though).
.
Apparently, the hall was supposed to be a 'gentleman's lounge' back in the old days. It has lounges where "the fellows can go up there and smoke cigars". We're not allowed to walk on the grass too since it's "reserved for the fellows". The professor also claims that the building is so old that it has no electricity (Everyone spotted that blinking CCTV and motion sensor up there though)
.
Amazing experience, fanciest dinner I've ever had.

caption.text:
"Welcome to England! Come on in!", said the campus porter. Apparently, the ancient, giant medieval doors are now card-locked so he had to be in front of the door for my arrival. Kept his bright smile on even under heavy rain and cold temperature.

I honestly feel very privileged being able to live inside the University of Cambridge. Tons of tourists, denied entry into the university, encircle the college areas trying to take pictures of the campus building, yet here I am out and about inside the University. ...
By the way, that picture of a tree is known as the tree that dropped an apple on Sir Isaac Newton, since he's a University of Cambridge alumnus. Definitely just a fun rumor for tourist attraction but still interesting to know. Well, because I'm basically 50% student 50% tourist.
Sarjana Natuna
